Count 1:  COURT ORDERS defendant to serve 9 months at the House of Correction with 54 days credit; pay mandatory costs, assessments and surcharges or a civil judgment is to be entered against the defendant and subject to other collection.

Count 2:  COURT ORDERS defendant to serve a term in the Wisconsin State Prison system - TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE - 43 months with 54 days credit; INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT - 13 months; EXTENDED SUPERVISION - 30 months - concurrent with Count 1; pay mandatory costs, assessments and surcharges by the end of the sentence or a civil judgment is to be entered against the defendant and subject to other collection.

Court finds defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  1) no violations of criminal law rising to the level of probable cause; 2) pay any monetary amounts ordered but not paid while in the institution; 3) no contact with C.P. (DOB: 6-3-04); 4) no alcohol or illegally controlled substances; 5) random screening; 6) seek and maintain employment; sex offender treatment or counseling; 7) absolute sobriety. 

COURT ORDERS:
- DOC to collect monetary sums/amounts at the rate of 25% of prison funds;
- defendant to provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis and pay the mandatory DNA surcharge;
- restitution set at -0-;
- no contact with C.P. (DOB: 6-3-04) during the entire length of the sentence.   Court advised defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Appeal rights given.  Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence, Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief and Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgment received and filed.  Copies given to the defendant.
